==English==
===Pronunciation===
*bīt, /baɪt/, /<tt>baIt</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[bite]], [[byte]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

=== Noun ===

'''bight'''

#A corner, bend, or angle; a [[hollow]]; as, the bight of a horse's knee; the bight of an elbow.
:#''I spied a bight of meadow some way below the roadway in an angle of the river.'' (Robert Louis Stevenson, ''[[:s:Travels with a Donkey in the Cévennes|Travels with a Donkey in the Cévennes]]'')
#An [[area]] of [[sea]] lying between two [[promontories]]; [[larger]] than a [[bay]], [[wider]] than a [[gulf]]
#A [[loop]] in a [[rope]].

